{
  "info": {
    "name": "P(l)otHole API",
    "description": "Complete test collection for the P(l)otHole road hazard API.\n\n## Auth\nIn development the server reads `x-dev-user-id` to identify the caller. Set the collection variable `userId` to the UUID of any seeded user. Run the **Setup – capture IDs** folder first to populate `hazardId` and `userId` automatically.\n\n## Variables\n| Variable | Default | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `baseUrl` | `http://localhost:3000/api/v1` | API root |\n| `userId` | *(set after seed)* | Authenticated user id |\n| `modUserId` | *(set after seed)* | Moderator user id |\n| `hazardId` | *(auto-set)* | Hazard used by single-resource tests |\n| `newHazardId` | *(auto-set)* | Hazard created during POST test |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl",    "value": "http://localhost:3000/api/v1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "userId",     "value": "", "type": "string",
      "description": "UUID of an ordinary seeded user (alice_spotter). Paste after running db:seed." },
    { "key": "modUserId",  "value": "", "type": "string",
      "description": "UUID of the moderator seeded user (city_mod). Paste after running db:seed." },
    { "key": "hazardId",   "value": "", "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated by the 'List Hazards' pre-test script." },
    { "key": "newHazardId","value": "", "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated after POST /hazards." }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Hazards",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Hazards (no auth)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Has data array', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('data').that.is.an('array');",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('hasMore');",
                  "  if (body.data.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('hazardId', body.data[0].id);",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/hazards",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["hazards"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Hazards – filter by type",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('All results are potholes', () => {",
                  "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
                  "  data.forEach(h => pm.expect(h.type).to.equal('pothole'));",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/hazards?type=pothole&sort=severity&limit=5",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["hazards"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "type",         "value": "pothole" },
                { "key": "sort",         "value": "severity" },
                { "key": "limit",        "value": "5" }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Hazards – filter by repairStatus",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/hazards?repairStatus=reported&sort=newest&limit=10",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["hazards"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "repairStatus", "value": "reported" },
                { "key": "sort",         "value": "newest" },
                { "key": "limit",        "value": "10" }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Hazards – filter by city",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
